    Climate data in tidychangepoint Using Taimal's algorithm

    Extract changepoints

    changepoints.Rd

    Not to be confused with wbs::changepoints(), which returns different information.

    Usage

    # S3 method for mod_default
changepoints(x, ...)

# S3 method for seg_default
changepoints(x, ...)

# S3 method for tidycpt
changepoints(x, ...)

changepoints_labels(x, ...)

changepoints(x, ...)

# S3 method for default
changepoints(x, ...)

params(x, ...)

# S3 method for ga
changepoints(x, ...)

# S3 method for cpt
changepoints(x, ...)

# S3 method for wbs
changepoints(x, ...)

    Arguments

    x

    A tidycpt object

    ...

    arguments passed to methods

    See also

    wbs::changepoints()

    Other tidychangepoint-generics: diagnose.seg_default(), exceedances(), fitness.seg_default()

    Other tidychangepoint-generics: diagnose.seg_default(), exceedances(), fitness.seg_default()

cpts <- segment(DataCPSim, method = "pelt")
#> method: pelt
changepoints(cpts)
#> [1] 547 822 972

cpts <- segment(DataCPSim, method = "wbs")
#> method: wbs
changepoints(cpts$segmenter)
